:\"manifest\",\"href\":\"/manifest.json\"}],[\"$\",\"meta\",null,{\"name\":\"theme-color\",\"content\":\"#7c3aed\"}],[\"$\",\"link\",null,{\"rel\":\"preconnect\",\"href\":\"https://fonts.googleapis.com\"}],[\"$\",\"link\",null,{\"rel\":\"preconnect\",\"href\":\"https://fonts.gstatic.com\",\"crossOrigin\":\"\"}],[\"$\",\"link\",null,{\"href\":\"https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Inter:wght@400;500;600;700;800&display=swap\",\"rel\":\"stylesheet\"}],[\"$\",\"link\",null,{\"rel\":\"stylesheet\",\"href\":\"https://cdnjs.cloudflare.com/ajax/libs/font-awesome/6.5.1/css/all.min.css\"}]]}],[\"$\",\"body\",null,{\"className\":\"min-h-screen flex flex-col\",\"children\":\"$L10\"}]]}]\n11:I[3024,[\"707\",\"static/chunks/707-a8cb8823e74114e8.js\",\"287\",\"static/chunks/287-f0778ca6bf51fa86.js\",\"145\",\"static/chunks/app/%5Blocale%5D/tools/s/%5Bslug%5D/page-62cbbf95a2da758e.js\"],\"default\"]\n5:[[\"$\",\"script\",null,{\"type\":\"application/ld+json\",\"dangerouslySetInnerHTML\":{\"__html\":\"{\\\"@context\\\":\\\"https://schema.org\\\",\\\"@type\\\":\\\"WebApplication\\\",\\\"name\\\":\\\"Convert JPG to WebP Online - Free\\\",\\\"description\\\":\\\"Convert JPG images to WebP format for smaller file sizes with the same quality. Perfect for web optimization.\\\",\\\"url\\\":\\\"https://toolpic.me/tools/s/convert-jpg-to-webp\\\",\\\"applicationCategory\\\":\\\"MultimediaApplication\\\",\\\"operatingSystem\\\":\\\"Any\\\",\\\"offers\\\":{\\\"@type\\\":\\\"Offer\\\",\\\"price\\\":\\\"0\\\",\\\"priceCurrency\\\":\\\"USD\\\"}}\"}}],[\"$\",\"script\",null,{\"type\":\"application/ld+json\",\"dangerouslySetInnerHTML\":{\"__html\":\"{\\\"@context\\\":\\\"https://schema.org\\\",\\\"@type\\\":\\\"BreadcrumbList\\\",\\\"itemListElement\\\":[{\\\"@type\\\":\\\"ListItem\\\",\\\"position\\\":1,\\\"name\\\":\\\"ToolPic\\\",\\\"item\\\":\\\"https://toolpic.me/en\\\"},{\\\"@type\\\":\\\"ListItem\\\",\\\"position\\\":2,\\\"name\\\":\\\"Convert JPG to WebP Online - Free\\\",\\\"item\\\":\\\"https://toolpic.me/tools/s/convert-jpg-to-webp\\\"}]}\"}}],[\"$\",\"$L11\",null,{\"toolId\":\"image-converter\",\"titleKey\":\"convertJpgToWebp\",\"descKey\":\"convertJpgToWebpDesc\"}]]\n12:I[3809,[\"707\",\"static/chunks/707-a8cb8823e74114e8.js\",\"465\",\"static/chunks/app/%5Blocale%5D/page-d5b8dc0a4bde352c.js\"],\"default\"]\n13:T436,There are two fundamental approaches to image compression: lossy and lossless. Understanding the difference helps you choose the right method for each situation.\n\nLossless compression reduces file size by finding and eliminating redundant data patterns without discarding any image information. When you decompress the file, you get back exactly the original pixel data. PNG uses lossless compression, making it ideal for graphics, logos, and screenshots where every detail matters. The downside is that lossless compression typically achieves only modest size reductions, usually between 10% and 40%.\n\nLossy compression achieves much greater size reductions by permanently removing image data that the human eye is unlikely to notice. JPEG is the most common lossy format, and modern formats like WebP offer even better lossy compression. At quality settings between 75% and 85%, most photographs are visually indistinguishable from the original while being 60% to 80% smaller. The key is finding the quality threshold where artifacts become noticeable for your specific image.10:[\"$\",\"$L12\",null,{\"formats\":\"$undefined\",\"locale\":\"en\",\"messages\":{\"meta\":{\"siteName\":\"ToolPic\",\"siteDescription\":\"Free online image and video tools. All processing happens in your browser - your files never leave your device.\",\"homeTitle\":\"Free Online Image & Video Tools | ToolPic\"},\"common\":{\"upload\":\"Upload files\",\"uploadHint\":\"or drag and drop files here\",\"download\":\"Download\",\"downloadAll\":\"Download all\",\"processing\":\"Processing...\",\"reset\":\"Reset\",\"privacy\":\"Your files are processed locally in your browser. Nothing is uploaded to any server.\",\"maxFileSize\":\"Max file size: {size}MB\",\"supportedFormats\":\"Supported formats: {formats}\",\"quality\":\"Quality\",\"width\":\"Width\",\"height\":\"Height\",\"format\":\"Output format\",\"start\":\"Start\",\"cancel\":\"Cancel\",\"done\":\"Done\",\"error\":\"An error occurred. Please try again.\",\"fileCount\":\"{count} file(s) selected\",\"originalSize\":\"Original: {size}\",\"newSize\":\"New: {size}\",\"savedPercent\":\"Saved {percent}%\"},\"nav\":{\"home\":\"Home\",\"imageTools\":\"Image Tools\",\"videoTools\":\"Video Tools\",\"allTools\":\"All Tools\",\"blog\":\"Blog\"},\"home\":{\"h1\":\"Free Online Image & Video Tools\",\"subtitle\":\"Compress, convert, and edit your media files instantly. No uploads, no sign-ups, no limits. 100% free and private.\",\"startNow\":\"Start Now\",\"learnMore\":\"Learn More\",\"imageSection\":\"Image Tools\",\"imageSectionDesc\":\"Powerful image editing and conversion utilities that run entirely in your browser.\",\"videoSection\":\"Video Tools\",\"videoSectionDesc\":\"Perform common video operations without uploading large files. All processing happens on your device.\",\"whyTitle\":\"Why ToolPic?\",\"whySubtitle\":\"Built with three core principles: privacy, accessibility, and speed.\",\"why1Title\":\"100% Browser-Based\",\"why1Desc\":\"All files are processed locally. Nothing is uploaded to any server. Your privacy is guaranteed.\",\"why2Title\":\"Free & Unlimited\",\"why2Desc\":\"No registration, no file limits, no watermarks. Use as much as you want, completely free.\",\"why3Title\":\"Fast & Easy\",\"why3Desc\":\"Simple drag-and-drop interface. Get results in seconds, no software installation needed.\"},\"tools\":{\"image-compressor\":{\"title\":\"Image Compressor\",\"description\":\"Compress JPEG, PNG, WebP images up to 80% without losing quality.\",\"h1\":\"Compress Images Online - Free & Fast\",\"metaTitle\":\"Free Image Compressor - Reduce Image Size Online | ToolPic\",\"metaDescription\":\"Compress JPEG, PNG, WebP, AVIF images online for free. Reduce file size up to 80% with smart compression. No upload, 100% browser-based.\",\"howToUseTitle\":\"How to Compress Images\",\"step1Title\":\"Upload Images\",\"step1Desc\":\"Drag and drop or click to select JPEG, PNG, or WebP images.\",\"step2Title\":\"Adjust Quality\",\"step2Desc\":\"Use the quality slider to balance between file size and image quality.\",\"step3Title\":\"Download Results\",\"step3Desc\":\"Download compressed images individually or all at once.\",\"featuresTitle\":\"Key Features\",\"feature1Title\":\"Smart Compression\",\"feature1Desc\":\"Advanced algorithms reduce file size up to 80% while maintaining visual quality.\",\"feature2Title\":\"Batch Processing\",\"feature2Desc\":\"Compress multiple images at once. No file count limits.\",\"feature3Title\":\"100% Private\",\"feature3Desc\":\"All processing happens in your browser. Your images never leave your device.\",\"feature4Title\":\"All Formats Supported\",\"feature4Desc\":\"Works with JPEG, PNG, WebP, and other common image formats.\",\"faqTitle\":\"Frequently Asked Questions\",\"faq1Q\":\"Does compressing an image reduce its quality?\",\"faq1A\":\"Smart compression removes unnecessary data while preserving visual quality. At 80% quality, most images look identical to the original but are significantly smaller.\",\"faq2Q\":\"Is there a file size limit?\",\"faq2A\":\"You can upload images up to 50MB each. There is no limit on the number of images you can compress.\",\"faq3Q\":\"Are my images uploaded to a server?\",\"faq3A\":\"No. All compression happens locally in your browser using WebAssembly technology. Your images never leave your device, ensuring complete privacy.\"},\"image-converter\":{\"title\":\"Image Converter\",\"description\":\"Convert images between JPG, PNG, WebP, AVIF, BMP formats instantly.\",\"h1\":\"Convert Image Format Online - Free\",\"metaTitle\":\"Free Image Converter - JPG PNG WebP AVIF Online | ToolPic\",\"metaDescription\":\"Convert images between JPG, PNG, WebP, AVIF, BMP, TIFF formats online for free. Fast and secure.\",\"howToUseTitle\":\"How to Convert Image Formats\",\"step1Title\":\"Upload Image\",\"step1Desc\":\"Drag and drop or select any JPG, PNG, WebP, AVIF, or BMP image.\",\"step2Title\":\"Choose Format\",\"step2Desc\":\"Select the target format you want to convert to from the dropdown menu.\",\"step3Title\":\"Download Converted File\",\"step3Desc\":\"Click download to save your image in the new format instantly.\",\"featuresTitle\":\"Key Features\",\"feature1Title\":\"Multiple Format Support\",\"feature1Desc\":\"Convert between JPG, PNG, WebP, AVIF, BMP, and TIFF formats with a single click.\",\"feature2Title\":\"Batch Conversion\",\"feature2Desc\":\"Convert multiple images at once. Save time with bulk format conversion.\",\"feature3Title\":\"Quality Preservation\",\"feature3Desc\":\"Converts images while maintaining the highest possible quality in the target format.\",\"feature4Title\":\"Instant Processing\",\"feature4Desc\":\"Browser-based conversion means no waiting for uploads or downloads from a server.\",\"faqTitle\":\"Frequently Asked Questions\",\"faq1Q\":\"Which image formats can I convert between?\",\"faq1A\":\"You can convert between JPG, PNG, WebP, AVIF, BMP, and TIFF formats. All conversions happen instantly in your browser.\",\"faq2Q\":\"Will converting an image reduce its quality?\",\"faq2A\":\"Converting to lossless formats like PNG preserves full quality. For lossy formats like JPG or WebP, you can adjust the quality setting to control the balance between file size and quality.\",\"faq3Q\":\"Why should I convert images to WebP?\",\"faq3A\":\"WebP provides superior compression compared to JPG and PNG, resulting in smaller file sizes with similar visual quality. It is widely supported by modern browsers and recommended for web use.\"},\"image-crop\":{\"title\":\"Image Crop & Resize\",\"description\":\"Crop and resize images with preset social media dimensions.\",\"h1\":\"Crop & Resize Images Online - Free\",\"metaTitle\":\"Free Image Cropper & Resizer Online | ToolPic\",\"metaDescription\":\"Crop and resize images online for free. Preset dimensions for social media. No upload needed.\",\"howToUseTitle\":\"How to Crop & Resize Images\",\"step1Title\":\"Upload Image\",\"step1Desc\":\"Drag and drop or click to select the image you want to crop or resize.\",\"step2Title\":\"Adjust Crop Area\",\"step2Desc\":\"Drag the crop handles or choose a preset aspect ratio for social media platforms.\",\"step3Title\":\"Download Result\",\"step3Desc\":\"Apply the crop and download your perfectly sized image.\",\"featuresTitle\":\"Key Features\",\"feature1Title\":\"Social Media Presets\",\"feature1Desc\":\"One-click presets for Instagram, Facebook, Twitter, YouTube thumbnails, and more.\",\"feature2Title\":\"Custom Aspect Ratios\",\"feature2Desc\":\"Set any custom width and height or lock aspect ratios for precise cropping.\",\"feature3Title\":\"Visual Crop Editor\",\"feature3Desc\":\"Intuitive drag-and-drop interface to select exactly the area you want to keep.\",\"feature4Title\":\"No Quality Loss\",\"feature4Desc\":\"Crop and resize without recompressing. Original image quality is fully preserved.\",\"faqTitle\":\"Frequently Asked Questions\",\"faq1Q\":\"What social media dimensions are supported?\",\"faq1A\":\"We include presets for Instagram posts (1080x1080), Instagram stories (1080x1920), Facebook covers (820x312), Twitter headers (1500x500), YouTube thumbnails (1280x720), and many more.\",\"faq2Q\":\"Can I resize an image without cropping?\",\"faq2A\":\"Yes. You can set custom width and height values to resize your image proportionally or to exact dimensions without cropping any part of it.\",\"faq3Q\":\"Does cropping reduce image quality?\",\"faq3A\":\"No. Cropping simply removes the parts of the image outside the selected area. The remaining portion retains its original quality.\"},\"image-watermark\":{\"title\":\"Add Watermark\",\"description\":\"Add text or image watermarks to your photos in batch.\",\"h1\":\"Add Watermark to Images Online - Free\",\"metaTitle\":\"Free Image Watermark Tool - Add Text/Logo Watermark | ToolPic\",\"metaDescription\":\"Add text or image watermarks to photos online for free. Batch processing supported. 100% browser-based.\",\"howToUseTitle\":\"How to Add Watermarks\",\"step1Title\":\"Upload Images\",\"step1Desc\":\"Drag and drop or select the photos you want to watermark.\",\"step2Title\":\"Customize Watermark\",\"step2Desc\":\"Add text or upload a logo. Adjust position, size, opacity, and rotation.\",\"step3Title\":\"Download Watermarked Images\",\"step3Desc\":\"Apply the watermark and download your protected images.\",\"featuresTitle\":\"Key Features\",\"feature1Title\":\"Text & Image Watermarks\",\"feature1Desc\":\"Add custom text with font styling or upload your own logo as a watermark.\",\"feature2Title\":\"Full Customization\",\"feature2Desc\":\"Control position, size, opacity, rotation, and color of your watermark with precision.\",\"feature3Title\":\"Batch Watermarking\",\"feature3Desc\":\"Apply the same watermark to multiple images at once. Perfect for photographers.\",\"feature4Title\":\"Protect Your Work\",\"feature4Desc\":\"Prevent unauthorized use of your photos by adding visible ownership marks.\",\"faqTitle\":\"Frequently Asked Questions\",\"faq1Q\":\"Can I use my own logo as a watermark?\",\"faq1A\":\"Yes. You can upload any PNG or JPG image as a watermark. PNG images with transparent backgrounds work best for logo watermarks.\",\"faq2Q\":\"Can I watermark multiple images at once?\",\"faq2A\":\"Yes. Upload multiple images and the same watermark settings will be applied to all of them. You can download all watermarked images at once.\",\"faq3Q\":\"Will the watermark affect image quality?\",\"faq3A\":\"The watermark is applied as an overlay without recompressing the base image. Your original image quality is maintained.\"},\"image-bg-remove\":{\"title\":\"Remove Background\",\"description\":\"AI-powered background removal. Get transparent PNG in seconds.\",\"h1\":\"Remove Image Background Online - Free AI Tool\",\"metaTitle\":\"Free Background Remover - AI Remove BG Online | ToolPic\",\"metaDescription\":\"Remove image background with AI online for free. Get transparent PNG in seconds. No upload, 100% private.\",\"howToUseTitle\":\"How to Remove Image Backgrounds\",\"step1Title\":\"Upload Image\",\"step1Desc\":\"Drag and drop or select the image whose background you want to remove.\",\"step2Title\":\"AI Processing\",\"step2Desc\":\"Our AI model automatically detects the subject and removes the background.\",\"step3Title\":\"Download Transparent PNG\",\"step3Desc\":\"Download your image with a transparent background as a PNG file.\",\"featuresTitle\":\"Key Features\",\"feature1Title\":\"AI-Powered Detection\",\"feature1Desc\":\"Advanced machine learning model accurately separates foreground subjects from backgrounds.\",\"feature2Title\":\"Instant Results\",\"feature2Desc\":\"Get a transparent PNG in seconds. No manual editing or selection tools needed.\",\"feature3Title\":\"Works with Any Subject\",\"feature3Desc\":\"People, products, animals, objects — the AI handles all types of subjects accurately.\",\"feature4Title\":\"Runs in Your Browser\",\"feature4Desc\":\"The AI model runs entirely in your browser using WebAssembly. Your images stay private.\",\"faqTitle\":\"Frequently Asked Questions\",\"faq1Q\":\"How does the AI background removal work?\",\"faq1A\":\"We use a neural network model that runs directly in your browser. It analyzes the image to identify the main subject and creates a precise mask to remove the background.\",\"faq2Q\":\"What types of images work best?\",\"faq2A\":\"The AI works best with clear subjects that have good contrast with the background. Photos of people, products, and animals typically produce excellent results.\",\"faq3Q\":\"Is my image sent to a server for processing?\",\"faq3A\":\"No. The AI model is loaded into your browser and all processing happens locally on your device. Your images are never uploaded to any server.\"},\"image-merge\":{\"title\":\"Merge Images\",\"description\":\"Combine multiple images into one. Create collages and long images.\",\"h1\":\"Merge Images Online - Free Collage Maker\",\"metaTitle\":\"Free Image Merger - Combine Photos Online | ToolPic\",\"metaDescription\":\"Merge and combine multiple images into one online for free. Create collages, long images. No upload needed.\",\"howToUseTitle\":\"How to Merge Images\",\"step1Title\":\"Upload Images\",\"step1Desc\":\"Drag and drop or select two or more images you want to combine.\",\"step2Title\":\"Arrange Layout\",\"step2Desc\":\"Choose horizontal, vertical, or grid layout. Adjust spacing and alignment.\",\"step3Title\":\"Download Merged Image\",\"step3Desc\":\"Export your combined image as a single file in your preferred format.\",\"featuresTitle\":\"Key Features\",\"feature1Title\":\"Flexible Layouts\",\"feature1Desc\":\"Merge images horizontally, vertically, or in a grid. Create long images or photo collages.\",\"feature2Title\":\"Custom Spacing\",\"feature2Desc\":\"Add padding and gaps between images. Choose background color for the spacing area.\",\"feature3Title\":\"Drag to Reorder\",\"feature3Desc\":\"Easily rearrange image order by dragging and dropping thumbnails.\",\"feature4Title\":\"No Image Limit\",\"feature4Desc\":\"Combine as many images as you need. No restrictions on the number of photos.\",\"faqTitle\":\"Frequently Asked Questions\",\"faq1Q\":\"How many images can I merge at once?\",\"faq1A\":\"There is no hard limit on the number of images. You can merge as many as your browser can handle. For best performance, we recommend merging up to 20 images at a time.\",\"faq2Q\":\"Can I merge images of different sizes?\",\"faq2A\":\"Yes. The tool automatically adjusts images to fit together. You can choose to match widths, heights, or keep original proportions.\",\"faq3Q\":\"What output format is the merged image?\",\"faq3A\":\"The merged image is saved as PNG by default to preserve quality. You can also choose JPG or WebP for smaller file sizes.\"},\"video-compress\":{\"title\":\"Video Compressor\",\"description\":\"Compress video files by adjusting resolution and bitrate.\",\"h1\":\"Compress Videos Online - Free & Fast\",\"metaTitle\":\"Free Video Compressor - Reduce Video Size Online | ToolPic\",\"metaDescription\":\"Compress MP4, WebM, AVI videos online for free. Reduce file size without losing quality. Browser-based.\",\"howToUseTitle\":\"How to Compress Videos\",\"step1Title\":\"Upload Video\",\"step1Desc\":\"Drag and drop or select an MP4, WebM, AVI, or MOV video file.\",\"step2Title\":\"Choose Settings\",\"step2Desc\":\"Adjust resolution, bitrate, and quality settings to control the output file size.\",\"step3Title\":\"Download Compressed Video\",\"step3Desc\":\"Wait for processing to complete, then download your smaller video file.\",\"featuresTitle\":\"Key Features\",\"feature1Title\":\"Significant Size Reduction\",\"feature1Desc\":\"Reduce video file size by up to 70% while maintaining watchable quality.\",\"feature2Title\":\"Resolution Control\",\"feature2Desc\":\"Downscale video resolution from 4K to 1080p, 720p, or 480p for smaller files.\",\"feature3Title\":\"Browser-Based Processing\",\"feature3Desc\":\"Videos are compressed locally using FFmpeg WebAssembly. No server uploads required.\",\"feature4Title\":\"Multiple Format Support\",\"feature4Desc\":\"Compress MP4, WebM, AVI, MOV, and MKV video files.\",\"faqTitle\":\"Frequently Asked Questions\",\"faq1Q\":\"How long does video compression take?\",\"faq1A\":\"Processing time depends on the video length, resolution, and your device's performance. A 1-minute 1080p video typically takes 30-60 seconds to compress.\",\"faq2Q\":\"What is the maximum video file size?\",\"faq2A\":\"Since processing happens in your browser, the limit depends on your device's available memory. Most devices can handle videos up to 500MB-1GB comfortably.\",\"faq3Q\":\"Will compression make my video look bad?\",\"faq3A\":\"With default settings, the visual quality difference is minimal. You can adjust the quality slider to find the perfect balance between file size and visual quality for your needs.\"},\"video-convert\":{\"title\":\"Video Converter\",\"description\":\"Convert videos between MP4, WebM, AVI, MOV formats.\",\"h1\":\"Convert Video Format Online - Free\",\"metaTitle\":\"Free Video Converter - MP4 WebM AVI MOV Online | ToolPic\",\"metaDescription\":\"Convert videos between MP4, WebM, AVI, MOV, MKV formats online for free. Fast browser-based conversion.\",\"howToUseTitle\":\"How to Convert Video Formats\",\"step1Title\":\"Upload Video\",\"step1Desc\":\"Drag and drop or select the video file you want to convert.\",\"step2Title\":\"Select Output Format\",\"step2Desc\":\"Choose your target format: MP4, WebM, AVI, MOV, or MKV.\",\"step3Title\":\"Download Converted Video\",\"step3Desc\":\"Wait for the conversion to finish, then download your video in the new format.\",\"featuresTitle\":\"Key Features\",\"feature1Title\":\"Wide Format Support\",\"feature1Desc\":\"Convert between MP4, WebM, AVI, MOV, and MKV formats for any device or platform.\",\"feature2Title\":\"Quality Settings\",\"feature2Desc\":\"Adjust video quality and codec settings to optimize for size or quality.\",\"feature3Title\":\"No Software Required\",\"feature3Desc\":\"Convert videos directly in your browser without installing any software.\",\"feature4Title\":\"Private & Secure\",\"feature4Desc\":\"Your video files never leave your device. All conversion happens locally using WebAssembly.\",\"faqTitle\":\"Frequently Asked Questions\",\"faq1Q\":\"Which video format should I choose?\",\"faq1A\":\"MP4 (H.264) is the most widely compatible format and works on virtually all devices and platforms. WebM is ideal for web use with smaller file sizes. MOV is preferred for Apple devices.\",\"faq2Q\":\"Can I convert large video files?\",\"faq2A\":\"Yes, but since conversion happens in your browser, performance depends on your device. Most devices handle files up to 500MB-1GB smoothly. For larger files, a desktop browser is recommended.\",\"faq3Q\":\"Does the conversion affect video quality?\",\"faq3A\":\"You can choose the output quality during conversion. With high quality settings, the difference from the original is negligible. Lower quality settings produce smaller files.\"},\"video-to-gif\":{\"title\":\"Video to GIF\",\"description\":\"Convert video clips to animated GIF with custom settings.\",\"h1\":\"Convert Video to GIF Online - Free\",\"metaTitle\":\"Free Video to GIF Converter Online | ToolPic\",\"metaDescription\":\"Convert video to GIF online for free. Customize frame rate, size, and duration. No software needed.\",\"howToUseTitle\":\"How to Convert Video to GIF\",\"step1Title\":\"Upload Video\",\"step1Desc\":\"Drag and drop or select an MP4, WebM, or other video file.\",\"step2Title\":\"Customize GIF Settings\",\"step2Desc\":\"Set the start time, duration, frame rate, and output size for your GIF.\",\"step3Title\":\"Download GIF\",\"step3Desc\":\"Generate and download your animated GIF file.\",\"featuresTitle\":\"Key Features\",\"feature1Title\":\"Trim & Select\",\"feature1Desc\":\"Choose the exact start point and duration of the video segment to convert into a GIF.\",\"feature2Title\":\"Frame Rate Control\",\"feature2Desc\":\"Adjust FPS to balance between smooth animation and smaller file size.\",\"feature3Title\":\"Resize Output\",\"feature3Desc\":\"Set custom width for your GIF. Smaller dimensions produce much smaller file sizes.\",\"feature4Title\":\"Preview Before Download\",\"feature4Desc\":\"See a preview of your GIF before downloading to make sure it looks exactly right.\",\"faqTitle\":\"Frequently Asked Questions\",\"faq1Q\":\"How can I make my GIF file smaller?\",\"faq1A\":\"Reduce the output width, lower the frame rate (10-12 FPS is usually sufficient), and keep the duration short. These three factors have the biggest impact on GIF file size.\",\"faq2Q\":\"What frame rate should I use?\",\"faq2A\":\"For most GIFs, 10-15 FPS provides smooth animation with reasonable file sizes. Higher frame rates create smoother motion but significantly larger files.\",\"faq3Q\":\"Is there a time limit for the video?\",\"faq3A\":\"There is no strict time limit, but GIFs are best suited for short clips (under 10 seconds). Longer GIFs result in very large file sizes that may be impractical to share.\"},\"video-extract-audio\":{\"title\":\"Extract Audio\",\"description\":\"Extract audio tracks from video files as MP3, WAV, or AAC.\",\"h1\":\"Extract Audio from Video Online - Free\",\"metaTitle\":\"Free Audio Extractor - Get MP3 from Video | ToolPic\",\"metaDescription\":\"Extract audio from video online for free. Save as MP3, WAV, or AAC. Fast browser-based extraction.\",\"howToUseTitle\":\"How to Extract Audio from Video\",\"step1Title\":\"Upload Video\",\"step1Desc\":\"Drag and drop or select the video file containing the audio you want to extract.\",\"step2Title\":\"Choose Audio Format\",\"step2Desc\":\"Select your preferred output format: MP3, WAV, or AAC.\",\"step3Title\":\"Download Audio File\",\"step3Desc\":\"Wait for extraction to complete, then download the audio file.\",\"featuresTitle\":\"Key Features\",\"feature1Title\":\"Multiple Audio Formats\",\"feature1Desc\":\"Export audio as MP3 for universal compatibility, WAV for lossless quality, or AAC for efficient compression.\",\"feature2Title\":\"Fast Extraction\",\"feature2Desc\":\"Audio extraction is faster than full video conversion since only the audio stream is processed.\",\"feature3Title\":\"All Video Formats\",\"feature3Desc\":\"Extract audio from MP4, WebM, AVI, MOV, MKV, and other common video formats.\",\"feature4Title\":\"High Quality Output\",\"feature4Desc\":\"Extract the original audio track without re-encoding for the best possible quality.\",\"faqTitle\":\"Frequently Asked Questions\",\"faq1Q\":\"Which audio format should I choose?\",\"faq1A\":\"MP3 is the most widely compatible format and works everywhere. WAV provides uncompressed lossless quality but creates larger files. AAC offers better quality than MP3 at similar file sizes.\",\"faq2Q\":\"Can I extract audio from a YouTube video?\",\"faq2A\":\"This tool works with video files on your device. You would need to first download the video file, then upload it here to extract the audio track.\",\"faq3Q\":\"Will the audio quality be the same as the original?\",\"faq3A\":\"When extracting to a lossless format like WAV, the audio quality matches the original. When extracting to MP3 or AAC, slight compression is applied but quality remains excellent at high bitrate settings.\"}},\"seoPages\":{\"privacy\":\"Your files are processed locally in your browser. Nothing is uploaded to any server.\",\"convertJpgToPng\":\"Convert JPG to PNG Online - Free\",\"convertJpgToPngDesc\":\"Convert JPG/JPEG images to PNG format online for free. Preserve transparency and quality. No upload needed, 100% browser-based.\",\"convertJpgToWebp\":\"Convert JPG to WebP Online - Free\",\"convertJpgToWebpDesc\":\"Convert JPG images to WebP format for smaller file sizes with the same quality. Perfect for web optimization.\",\"convertPngToJpg\":\"Convert PNG to JPG Online - Free\",\"convertPngToJpgDesc\":\"Convert PNG images to JPG format online for free. Reduce file size while maintaining visual quality. No software needed.\",\"convertPngToWebp\":\"Convert PNG to WebP Online - Free\",\"convertPngToWebpDesc\":\"Convert PNG images to WebP format for significantly smaller file sizes. Ideal for faster website loading.\",\"convertWebpToJpg\":\"Convert WebP to JPG Online - Free\",\"convertWebpToJpgDesc\":\"Convert WebP images to JPG format online for free. Make your images compatible with all devices and software.\",\"convertWebpToPng\":\"Convert WebP to PNG Online - Free\",\"convertWebpToPngDesc\":\"Convert WebP images to PNG format online for free. Get lossless quality with full transparency support.\",\"convertHeicToJpg\":\"Convert HEIC to JPG Online - Free\",\"convertHeicToJpgDesc\":\"Convert iPhone HEIC/HEIF photos to JPG format online for free. Make your Apple photos universally compatible.\",\"convertBmpToJpg\":\"Convert BMP to JPG Online - Free\",\"convertBmpToJpgDesc\":\"Convert BMP bitmap images to JPG format online for free. Dramatically reduce file size from uncompressed BMP files.\",\"convertMp4ToWebm\":\"Convert MP4 to WebM Online - Free\",\"convertMp4ToWebmDesc\":\"Convert MP4 videos to WebM format online for free. WebM offers smaller file sizes ideal for web embedding.\",\"convertMp4ToAvi\":\"Convert MP4 to AVI Online - Free\",\"convertMp4ToAviDesc\":\"Convert MP4 videos to AVI format online for free. AVI provides wide compatibility with older media players and editors.\",\"convertWebmToMp4\":\"Convert WebM to MP4 Online - Free\",\"convertWebmToMp4Desc\":\"Convert WebM videos to MP4 format online for free. MP4 is the most universally compatible video format.\",\"convertMp4ToGif\":\"Convert MP4 to GIF Online - Free\",\"convertMp4ToGifDesc\":\"Convert MP4 video clips to animated GIF online for free. Create shareable GIFs from any video. Custom frame rate and size.\",\"compressJpg\":\"Compress JPG Images Online - Free\",\"compressJpgDesc\":\"Compress JPG/JPEG images online for free. Reduce file size up to 80% without visible quality loss. No upload required.\",\"compressPng\":\"Compress PNG Images Online - Free\",\"compressPngDesc\":\"Compress PNG images online for free. Reduce PNG file size while preserving transparency and quality. 100% browser-based.\",\"compressWebp\":\"Compress WebP Images Online - Free\",\"compressWebpDesc\":\"Compress WebP images online for free. Optimize WebP file size for faster web performance without sacrificing quality.\",\"compressMp4\":\"Compress MP4 Videos Online - Free\",\"compressMp4Desc\":\"Compress MP4 video files online for free. Reduce video size by up to 70% while maintaining watchable quality. No server upload.\",\"resizeInstagram\":\"Resize Image for Instagram - Free Online Tool\",\"resizeInstagramDesc\":\"Resize and crop images to perfect Instagram dimensions online for free. Supports posts (1080x1080), stories (1080x1920), and reels.\",\"resizeFacebook\":\"Resize Image for Facebook - Free Online Tool\",\"resizeFacebookDesc\":\"Resize images for Facebook cover photos, profile pictures, and posts online for free. Get the perfect dimensions every time.\",\"resizeTwitter\":\"Resize Image for Twitter/X - Free Online Tool\",\"resizeTwitterDesc\":\"Resize images for Twitter/X headers (1500x500), posts, and profile pictures online for free. Optimized for the platform.\",\"resizeYoutube\":\"Resize Image for YouTube Thumbnail - Free\",\"resizeYoutubeDesc\":\"Create perfect YouTube thumbnails at 1280x720 pixels online for free. Crop and resize images to the ideal thumbnail size.\",\"removeBg\":\"Remove Image Background Online - Free AI Tool\",\"removeBgDesc\":\"Remove backgrounds from images online for free using AI. Get transparent PNG in seconds. Works with people, products, and objects.\",\"addWatermark\":\"Add Watermark to Photos Online - Free\",\"addWatermarkDesc\":\"Add text or logo watermarks to your photos online for free. Protect your images with custom watermarks. Batch processing supported.\",\"mergePhotos\":\"Merge Photos Online - Free Image Combiner\",\"mergePhotosDesc\":\"Combine and merge multiple photos into one image online for free. Create collages, side-by-side comparisons, and long images.\",\"extractMp3\":\"Extract MP3 from Video Online - Free\",\"extractMp3Desc\":\"Extract audio from video files and save as MP3 online for free. Works with MP4, WebM, AVI, and other video formats.\"},\"blog\":{\"title\":\"Blog\",\"subtitle\":\"Tips, guides, and tutorials for image and video processing\",\"readTime\":\"{minutes} min read\",\"relatedTools\":\"Related Tools\",\"posts\":{\"how-to-compress-images-without-losing-quality\":{\"title\":\"How to Compress Images Without Losing Quality\",\"metaTitle\":\"How to Compress Images Without Losing Quality | ToolPic Blog\",\"metaDescription\":\"Learn the best techniques to reduce image file size while maintaining visual quality. Practical guide with tips for JPEG, PNG, and WebP compression.\",\"excerpt\":\"Learn the best techniques to reduce image file size while maintaining visual quality for web and mobile.\",\"content\":[{\"heading\":\"Why Image Compression Matters\",\"text\":\"Large images are one of the biggest reasons websites load slowly. When a page takes more than three seconds to load, over half of visitors will leave before they even see your content. Search engines also factor page speed into their ranking algorithms, so heavy images can directly hurt your visibility in search results.\\n\\nBeyond website performance, compressed images are easier to share via email, messaging apps, and social media platforms that impose file size limits. A 5MB photo from your phone might look great on a high-resolution screen, but it is far larger than necessary for most online uses. Reducing it to 500KB or less can make it load ten times faster without any noticeable drop in visual quality.\\n\\nImage compression is especially important for e-commerce stores, portfolios, and content-heavy blogs where dozens of images appear on a single page. Even small savings per image add up to significant improvements in overall page performance.\"},{\"heading\":\"Lossy vs Lossless Compression\",\"text\":\"$13\"},{\"heading\":\"Best Practices for Image Compression\",\"text\":\"Start by choosing the right format for your content. Use JPEG or WebP for photographs and complex images with gradients. Use PNG for graphics with sharp edges, text overlays, or transparency. Avoid using PNG for photographs, as it produces unnecessarily large files.\\n\\nResize images to the dimensions they will actually be displayed at before compressing them. There is no point in serving a 4000-pixel-wide image to a container that is only 800 pixels wide. Resizing first and then compressing is far more effective than compressing alone.\\n\\nFor web use, aim for file sizes under 200KB for hero images and under 100KB for thumbnails and content images. Use quality settings between 75% and 85% for JPEG and WebP. Always compare the compressed version side by side with the original to ensure the quality meets your standards.\"},{\"heading\":\"How to Compress Images with ToolPic\",\"text\":\"Step 1: Open the Image Compressor tool on ToolPic. You can drag and drop your images directly onto the upload area, or click to browse your files. Multiple images can be processed at once.\\n\\nStep 2: Adjust the quality slider to set your desired compression level. The default setting of 80% works well for most photographs. Move the slider lower for smaller files or higher to preserve more detail. The tool shows the estimated file size reduction in real time.\\n\\nStep 3: Once processing is complete, review the before-and-after comparison to verify the quality is acceptable. Download individual images or use the \\\"Download All\\\" button to save everything at once. Your files never leave your browser, so the entire process is completely private.\"}],\"relatedToolIds\":\"image-compressor\"},\"jpg-vs-png-vs-webp-which-image-format\":{\"title\":\"JPG vs PNG vs WebP: Which Image Format Should You Use?\",\"metaTitle\":\"JPG vs PNG vs WebP: Which Image Format Should You Use? | ToolPic Blog\",\"metaDescription\":\"Compare JPG, PNG, and WebP image formats. Learn when to use each format based on quality, file size, transparency, and browser support.\",\"excerpt\":\"A practical comparison of JPG, PNG, and WebP formats to help you choose the right one for every situation.\",\"content\":[{\"heading\":\"Understanding Image Formats\",\"text\":\"Choosing the right image format can make a significant difference in file size, loading speed, and visual quality. Each format was designed for different use cases, and using the wrong one often means unnecessarily large files or degraded image quality.\\n\\nThe three most important formats for the web today are JPEG (JPG), PNG, and WebP. JPEG has been the standard for photographs since the mid-1990s. PNG became the go-to format for graphics and images requiring transparency. WebP, developed by Google, is a modern format that aims to replace both by offering better compression for both photographic and graphic content.\\n\\nUnderstanding the strengths and limitations of each format is essential for anyone working with images, whether you are building a website, managing social media content, or simply trying to save storage space on your devices.\"},{\"heading\":\"JPEG: The Photography Standard\",\"text\":\"JPEG uses lossy compression that excels at representing photographs and images with smooth color transitions. It can reduce photo file sizes by 80% or more while maintaining excellent visual quality at moderate compression levels.\\n\\nThe main advantage of JPEG is its universal compatibility. Every device, browser, and application supports it. It is also highly configurable, allowing you to choose a quality level anywhere from minimal compression to aggressive reduction.\\n\\nHowever, JPEG has notable limitations. It does not support transparency, so you cannot place a JPEG image over a different background without a visible rectangle around it. It also introduces visible artifacts at lower quality settings, particularly around sharp edges and text. Each time you edit and resave a JPEG, the quality degrades further due to recompression.\"},{\"heading\":\"PNG: Lossless Quality and Transparency\",\"text\":\"PNG uses lossless compression, meaning the image quality is perfectly preserved regardless of how many times you save it. It also supports full alpha transparency, allowing pixels to be partially or fully transparent.\\n\\nThis makes PNG the best choice for logos, icons, screenshots, graphics with text, and any image where you need a transparent background. It is also ideal for images that will be edited multiple times, since there is no quality loss from repeated saving.\\n\\nThe trade-off is file size. PNG files are typically three to five times larger than JPEG files for photographic content. This makes PNG impractical for large photographs on the web, where loading speed is critical. Use PNG when quality and transparency matter more than file size.\"},{\"heading\":\"WebP: The Modern Choice\",\"text\":\"WebP was developed by Google to provide superior compression for web images. It supports both lossy and lossless compression, as well as transparency and animation, effectively combining the best features of JPEG, PNG, and GIF into a single format.\\n\\nIn practice, WebP lossy images are typically 25% to 35% smaller than JPEG at equivalent visual quality. WebP lossless images are about 26% smaller than PNG. This makes WebP an excellent default choice for web use, reducing bandwidth costs and improving page load times.\\n\\nBrowser support for WebP is now excellent, covering Chrome, Firefox, Safari, and Edge. The main limitation is compatibility with older software and some native mobile apps. When maximum compatibility is required, JPEG remains the safer choice. For web publishing where performance matters, WebP is the clear winner. You can use ToolPic's Image Converter to easily switch between any of these formats.\"}],\"relatedToolIds\":\"image-converter\"},\"how-to-convert-video-to-gif\":{\"title\":\"How to Convert Video to GIF: Complete Guide\",\"metaTitle\":\"How to Convert Video to GIF: Complete Guide | ToolPic Blog\",\"metaDescription\":\"Learn how to convert video clips to GIF format with optimized settings. Tips for frame rate, resolution, and file size.\",\"excerpt\":\"Everything you need to know about converting video clips to high-quality GIFs with manageable file sizes.\",\"content\":[{\"heading\":\"Why GIFs Remain Popular\",\"text\":\"Despite being a format from 1987, GIFs have become more popular than ever. They play automatically in almost every messaging app, social media platform, and email client without requiring a video player. This seamless playback makes them perfect for reactions, demonstrations, and quick tutorials.\\n\\nGIFs are also widely used for product demos, UI animations, and bug reports in professional contexts. A short GIF showing a software feature in action communicates more effectively than paragraphs of text or a series of static screenshots.\\n\\nThe format's main limitation is file size. Because GIFs use a relatively inefficient compression method and are limited to 256 colors per frame, they can quickly become large. A well-optimized 5-second GIF might be 1-2MB, while a poorly configured one could easily exceed 10MB.\"},{\"heading\":\"Choosing the Right Settings\",\"text\":\"The three most important settings when converting video to GIF are duration, frame rate, and output dimensions. Getting these right makes the difference between a crisp, shareable GIF and an unwieldy file that takes forever to load.\\n\\nKeep your GIF duration short. Anything under 5 seconds is ideal, and most effective GIFs are between 2 and 4 seconds. Longer clips should be trimmed to focus on the most important moment.\\n\\nFrame rate has a huge impact on file size. Videos typically run at 24-30 frames per second, but GIFs look smooth at just 10-15 FPS. Dropping from 30 FPS to 12 FPS cuts the file size by more than half with minimal visual impact. For simple animations, even 8 FPS can work well.\"},{\"heading\":\"Optimizing GIF File Size\",\"text\":\"Resolution is the single biggest factor in GIF file size. A 1080p GIF will be enormous. For most uses, a width of 480 to 640 pixels is sufficient. Social media platforms and messaging apps display GIFs at small sizes anyway, so high resolution is wasted.\\n\\nColor reduction also helps. GIFs support a maximum of 256 colors per frame. If your source video has many colors, the conversion process must choose which 256 to keep. Simpler scenes with fewer colors naturally produce smaller files.\\n\\nFinally, consider whether you truly need a GIF. Modern alternatives like WebP animations and short MP4 loops produce much smaller files with better quality. However, GIFs remain the most universally compatible option for animated images across all platforms.\"},{\"heading\":\"Creating GIFs with ToolPic\",\"text\":\"Open the Video to GIF tool on ToolPic and upload your video file. The tool supports MP4, WebM, and other common video formats. Use the timeline slider to select the exact start point and duration of the clip you want to convert.\\n\\nSet your desired output width. For social media and messaging, 480px is a good starting point. Adjust the frame rate to 10-12 FPS unless you need smoother motion. The tool previews the estimated file size so you can fine-tune settings before converting.\\n\\nOnce you are satisfied with the preview, click convert and download your optimized GIF. The entire process happens in your browser, so your video files stay completely private on your device.\"}],\"relatedToolIds\":\"video-to-gif\"},\"best-image-compression-tools-2026\":{\"title\":\"5 Best Free Image Compression Tools in 2026\",\"metaTitle\":\"5 Best Free Image Compression Tools in 2026 | ToolPic Blog\",\"metaDescription\":\"Compare the best free image compression tools in 2026. Browser-based vs desktop options, privacy features, and compression quality compared.\",\"excerpt\":\"An honest comparison of the top free image compression tools available in 2026, including browser-based and desktop options.\",\"content\":[{\"heading\":\"What Makes a Good Compression Tool\",\"text\":\"A good image compression tool should balance three things: compression ratio, visual quality, and ease of use. The best tools let you reduce file sizes significantly while keeping images visually indistinguishable from the originals at normal viewing sizes.\\n\\nPrivacy is also an increasingly important consideration. Tools that process images on their servers require you to upload your files, which means your images pass through a third-party system. For sensitive or proprietary images, browser-based tools that process everything locally offer a clear advantage.\\n\\nOther factors worth considering include batch processing support, format options, maximum file size limits, and whether the tool adds watermarks or requires registration. The tools listed here all offer free tiers with practical functionality.\"},{\"heading\":\"Browser-Based Tools\",\"text\":\"ToolPic processes images entirely in your browser using WebAssembly technology. Your files never leave your device, making it the most privacy-friendly option available. It supports JPEG, PNG, WebP, and AVIF formats with adjustable quality settings and batch processing. There are no file count limits or watermarks.\\n\\nSquoosh, developed by the Google Chrome team, is an excellent single-image compression tool. It offers a unique side-by-side comparison view and supports modern formats including AVIF and JPEG XL. However, it only processes one image at a time, making it less practical for batch work.\\n\\nTinyPNG is a popular web-based tool that handles both PNG and JPEG compression well. It uses smart lossy compression that produces excellent results. The free version limits you to 20 images per batch and 5MB per image, and images are uploaded to their servers for processing.\"},{\"heading\":\"Desktop and CLI Tools\",\"text\":\"ImageOptim is a free desktop application for macOS that compresses images using multiple optimization algorithms. It is particularly good at optimizing PNG files and can process entire folders at once. Being a native application, it handles large batches faster than browser-based tools.\\n\\nSharpJS is a high-performance Node.js image processing library that developers can integrate into their build pipelines. It offers excellent compression quality and supports all major formats. While it requires technical knowledge to set up, it is ideal for automating image optimization in web development workflows.\\n\\nFor most users, browser-based tools offer the best combination of convenience and quality. They require no installation, work on any operating system, and provide immediate results. Desktop tools are better suited for professional workflows that require processing thousands of images regularly.\"},{\"heading\":\"Privacy Comparison\",\"text\":\"When choosing a compression tool, consider where your images are being processed. Server-based tools like TinyPNG upload your images to remote servers for processing. While reputable services delete files after processing, your images do briefly exist on third-party infrastructure.\\n\\nBrowser-based tools like ToolPic and Squoosh never upload your files. All processing happens locally using your device's CPU and memory. This makes them the clear choice for confidential images, client work, personal photos, and any content you do not want leaving your device.\\n\\nFor professional photographers, e-commerce businesses handling product images, and anyone working with proprietary content, browser-based processing eliminates the risk of data exposure entirely. The quality of browser-based compression has improved dramatically and now matches or exceeds most server-based alternatives.\"}],\"relatedToolIds\":\"image-compressor\"},\"how-to-remove-image-background-free\":{\"title\":\"How to Remove Image Background for Free Online\",\"metaTitle\":\"How to Remove Image Background for Free Online | ToolPic Blog\",\"metaDescription\":\"Learn how to remove image backgrounds for free using AI-powered online tools. Tips for e-commerce, social media, and professional use.\",\"excerpt\":\"Remove image backgrounds instantly with free AI-powered tools. Perfect for product photos, social media, and professional content.\",\"content\":[{\"heading\":\"How AI Background Removal Works\",\"text\":\"Modern background removal tools use deep learning models that have been trained on millions of images to distinguish foreground subjects from backgrounds. These neural networks analyze the image to identify edges, depth cues, and contextual information to create precise cutout masks.\\n\\nThe technology has improved dramatically in recent years. Earlier tools required manual selection with magic wand or lasso tools and struggled with complex edges like hair or fur. Today's AI models handle these challenging cases automatically, producing clean cutouts in seconds that would have taken minutes of careful manual editing.\\n\\nSome tools process images on remote servers, sending your photos to cloud infrastructure for AI processing. Others, like ToolPic, run the AI model directly in your browser using WebAssembly, keeping your images completely private while still delivering professional-quality results.\"},{\"heading\":\"Common Use Cases\",\"text\":\"E-commerce product photography is one of the most popular applications. Clean white or transparent backgrounds are standard for marketplaces like Amazon, eBay, and Shopify stores. Instead of setting up a professional photo studio, sellers can photograph products against any background and remove it digitally.\\n\\nSocial media content creation frequently requires transparent backgrounds for layering images, creating collages, or placing subjects in new settings. Profile pictures, marketing graphics, and branded content all benefit from clean cutouts.\\n\\nProfessional designers use background removal as a starting point for compositing work, placing subjects into new environments, creating promotional materials, or preparing images for print where specific background colors or patterns are required.\"},{\"heading\":\"Tips for Best Results\",\"text\":\"The quality of your results depends partly on the input image. Photos with good contrast between the subject and background produce the cleanest cutouts. Well-lit images with sharp focus give the AI model clear edges to work with.\\n\\nAvoid images where the subject color closely matches the background color. A person wearing a green shirt against green foliage will be harder for any tool to process accurately than the same person against a plain wall.\\n\\nFor product photography, use a contrasting background when shooting. Even though you plan to remove the background later, starting with good contrast helps the AI produce cleaner edges. A simple white or gray backdrop works well for most products.\"},{\"heading\":\"Using ToolPic for Background Removal\",\"text\":\"Open the Remove Background tool on ToolPic and upload your image. The AI model loads in your browser on first use, which takes a few seconds. After that, processing is nearly instant for subsequent images.\\n\\nThe tool automatically detects the main subject and removes the background, producing a transparent PNG. Review the result and download the image. For batch processing, you can upload multiple images and process them sequentially.\\n\\nSince the AI runs entirely in your browser, your images are never sent to any server. This makes it safe to use with confidential product photos, personal images, or client work without any privacy concerns.\"}],\"relatedToolIds\":\"image-bg-remove\"},\"reduce-video-file-size-for-email\":{\"title\":\"How to Reduce Video File Size for Email & Sharing\",\"metaTitle\":\"How to Reduce Video File Size for Email & Sharing | ToolPic Blog\",\"metaDescription\":\"Learn how to reduce video file size for email attachments and sharing. Understand resolution, bitrate, and format choices for optimal compression.\",\"excerpt\":\"Practical techniques to shrink video files for email attachments, messaging apps, and social media sharing.\",\"content\":[{\"heading\":\"Why Video Files Are So Large\",\"text\":\"Video files are large because they contain a sequence of images (frames) played back at 24 to 60 frames per second, along with audio data. A single minute of uncompressed 1080p video at 30 FPS would require roughly 10GB of storage, which is why video compression is essential.\\n\\nModern video codecs like H.264 and H.265 use sophisticated compression techniques to reduce this dramatically. They store the differences between consecutive frames rather than each frame independently, achieving compression ratios of 100:1 or better while maintaining good visual quality.\\n\\nDespite this compression, everyday video files remain large by email standards. A one-minute 1080p clip recorded on a smartphone typically ranges from 100MB to 200MB, far exceeding the 25MB attachment limit that most email providers enforce.\"},{\"heading\":\"Understanding Resolution and Bitrate\",\"text\":\"Resolution and bitrate are the two main levers for controlling video file size. Resolution refers to the number of pixels in each frame. Common resolutions include 4K (3840x2160), 1080p (1920x1080), 720p (1280x720), and 480p (854x480). Halving the resolution reduces the pixel count by 75%, which dramatically reduces file size.\\n\\nBitrate is the amount of data used per second of video. Higher bitrate means more data and better quality, while lower bitrate means smaller files with potentially visible compression artifacts. For web sharing, a bitrate of 2-4 Mbps for 1080p content offers a good balance.\\n\\nFor email attachments, reducing resolution to 720p or 480p is usually the most effective approach. Most recipients will watch on their phone or in a small email preview, where the lower resolution is perfectly acceptable.\"},{\"heading\":\"Choosing the Right Format\",\"text\":\"MP4 with H.264 encoding is the most universally compatible video format. It plays on virtually every device and platform without requiring additional software. For sharing via email or messaging, MP4 should be your default choice.\\n\\nWebM offers better compression efficiency than H.264, meaning smaller files at the same quality level. However, compatibility is less universal, particularly with older devices and some email clients. Use WebM when you know the recipient can play it.\\n\\nFor the smallest possible file size, H.265 (HEVC) provides about 50% better compression than H.264 at the same quality. Support is widespread on modern devices but not universal. If maximum compatibility matters more than minimum file size, stick with H.264 MP4.\"},{\"heading\":\"Step-by-Step Compression with ToolPic\",\"text\":\"Open the Video Compressor tool on ToolPic and drag your video file onto the upload area. The tool accepts MP4, WebM, AVI, MOV, and other common formats.\\n\\nChoose your target resolution. For email sharing, 720p is usually the sweet spot between quality and file size. For messaging apps, 480p is often sufficient. Adjust the quality slider to control the bitrate. The medium setting works well for most content.\\n\\nClick compress and wait for the processing to complete. The tool shows progress and the resulting file size. Download the compressed video and verify it plays correctly before attaching it to your email. All processing happens locally in your browser, so your video content remains private.\"}],\"relatedToolIds\":\"video-compress\"},\"image-sizes-for-social-media-guide\":{\"title\":\"Social Media Image Sizes Guide 2026: Instagram, Facebook, Twitter\",\"metaTitle\":\"Social Media Image Sizes Guide 2026 | ToolPic Blog\",\"metaDescription\":\"Complete guide to social media image sizes in 2026. Recommended dimensions for Instagram, Facebook, Twitter/X, YouTube, LinkedIn, and TikTok.\",\"excerpt\":\"The complete reference for social media image dimensions in 2026, covering all major platforms and placement types.\",\"content\":[{\"heading\":\"Why Image Dimensions Matter\",\"text\":\"Social media platforms display images at specific aspect ratios and resolutions. When you upload an image that does not match the expected dimensions, the platform will crop it automatically. This often cuts off important parts of your image, such as text, product details, or parts of a person's face.\\n\\nUsing the correct dimensions ensures your images display exactly as intended across all devices. It also prevents the platform from applying additional compression to resize your image, which can reduce visual quality.\\n\\nEach platform has different requirements for different placements. A profile picture has different dimensions than a cover photo, which differs from a post image. Keeping track of all these sizes is essential for anyone managing social media content professionally.\"},{\"heading\":\"Instagram Dimensions\",\"text\":\"Instagram square posts should be 1080 x 1080 pixels. This is the classic Instagram format and works well for most content. Portrait posts perform best at 1080 x 1350 pixels (4:5 ratio), which takes up more screen space in the feed and tends to generate higher engagement.\\n\\nInstagram Stories and Reels use a 9:16 vertical format at 1080 x 1920 pixels. This fills the entire phone screen. Profile pictures are displayed in a circle at 320 x 320 pixels, though uploading at a higher resolution like 500 x 500 ensures sharpness on high-density displays.\\n\\nCarousel posts can use any of the standard post sizes, but all images in a carousel must share the same aspect ratio. The first image determines the aspect ratio for the entire carousel.\"},{\"heading\":\"Facebook, Twitter/X, and YouTube\",\"text\":\"Facebook cover photos should be 820 x 312 pixels on desktop, but they display differently on mobile (640 x 360), so keep important content centered. Profile pictures are 170 x 170 pixels on desktop. Shared images in the feed work best at 1200 x 630 pixels.\\n\\nTwitter/X header images should be 1500 x 500 pixels. Profile photos are 400 x 400 pixels. In-tweet images display best at 1200 x 675 pixels (16:9 ratio). Single image tweets can also use 1200 x 1200 for square format.\\n\\nYouTube thumbnails should be exactly 1280 x 720 pixels with a minimum width of 640 pixels. Channel banners are 2560 x 1440 pixels, but the safe area for text and logos is the center 1546 x 423 pixels, as the rest may be cropped on different devices.\"},{\"heading\":\"How to Resize Images with ToolPic\",\"text\":\"Open the Image Crop & Resize tool on ToolPic and upload your image. The tool includes built-in presets for all major social media platforms, so you do not need to remember specific dimensions.\\n\\nSelect the platform and placement type from the preset menu. The tool automatically sets the correct aspect ratio and dimensions. Position the crop area over the part of your image you want to keep, then apply the crop.\\n\\nDownload the perfectly sized image ready for upload. You can process multiple images in sequence without reloading the page. The crop tool preserves original image quality and processes everything locally in your browser.\"}],\"relatedToolIds\":\"image-crop\"},\"what-is-webp-format-and-why-use-it\":{\"title\":\"What is WebP Format? Why You Should Use It in 2026\",\"metaTitle\":\"What is WebP Format? Why You Should Use It in 2026 | ToolPic Blog\",\"metaDescription\":\"Learn what WebP image format is, its advantages over JPEG and PNG, browser support status, and how to convert your images to WebP.\",\"excerpt\":\"Everything you need to know about the WebP image format: its advantages, browser support, and how to start using it today.\",\"content\":[{\"heading\":\"What is WebP\",\"text\":\"WebP is an image format developed by Google and released in 2010 as a modern replacement for JPEG, PNG, and GIF. It uses advanced compression algorithms derived from the VP8 and VP9 video codecs to achieve significantly smaller file sizes compared to older formats.\\n\\nThe format supports both lossy and lossless compression modes. In lossy mode, WebP produces files that are typically 25-35% smaller than JPEG at the same visual quality. In lossless mode, WebP files are about 26% smaller than PNG files. It also supports transparency (alpha channel) and animation, making it a versatile replacement for JPEG, PNG, and GIF.\\n\\nWebP was specifically designed for the web, where smaller file sizes translate directly into faster page loads, lower bandwidth costs, and better user experience, especially on mobile connections.\"},{\"heading\":\"Advantages Over JPEG and PNG\",\"text\":\"The primary advantage of WebP is compression efficiency. For photographic images, a WebP file at 80% quality is visually equivalent to a JPEG at 85-90% quality but 30% smaller in file size. For a website with hundreds of images, this adds up to meaningful bandwidth savings and faster load times.\\n\\nUnlike JPEG, WebP supports transparency without the file size penalty of PNG. A product image with a transparent background saved as WebP is typically 3-5 times smaller than the equivalent PNG file. This makes WebP ideal for e-commerce sites where transparent product images are common.\\n\\nWebP also supports animation as an alternative to GIF. Animated WebP files are significantly smaller than equivalent GIFs while supporting full 24-bit color instead of GIF's 256-color limit. For websites that use animated elements, switching from GIF to WebP can reduce file sizes by 50% or more.\"},{\"heading\":\"Browser Support in 2026\",\"text\":\"As of 2026, WebP is supported by all major browsers including Chrome, Firefox, Safari, Edge, and Opera. Safari added WebP support in version 14 (2020), which was the last major holdout. This means WebP now works reliably for over 97% of web users worldwide.\\n\\nMobile browser support is equally comprehensive. Both iOS Safari and Android Chrome fully support WebP, making it safe to use for mobile web experiences without fallbacks.\\n\\nThe remaining compatibility concerns are primarily with older desktop software. Some image editors, email clients, and content management systems may not handle WebP files natively. For these cases, keeping a JPEG or PNG version available as a fallback is a practical solution. Most modern web development workflows generate both WebP and fallback formats automatically.\"},{\"heading\":\"How to Convert Images to WebP\",\"text\":\"Converting your existing images to WebP is straightforward with ToolPic's Image Converter. Upload any JPEG, PNG, BMP, or AVIF image and select WebP as the output format. The tool preserves transparency from PNG sources and lets you adjust the quality level for lossy conversion.\\n\\nFor best results, start with the highest quality source image available. Converting from a heavily compressed JPEG to WebP will not magically improve quality. If you have the original uncompressed or losslessly compressed version, convert from that for optimal results.\\n\\nWhen migrating a website to WebP, use the HTML picture element or CSS image-set to serve WebP to supported browsers while providing JPEG or PNG fallbacks for older clients. Most CDN providers and build tools can automate this process. The initial effort of converting to WebP pays for itself quickly through reduced bandwidth costs and improved page performance.\"}],\"relatedToolIds\":\"image-converter\"}}},\"footer\":{\"tagline\":\"Free online tools for images and videos. 100% browser-based, your files never leave your device.\",\"tools\":\"Tools\",\"legal\":\"Legal\",\"privacy\":\"Privacy Policy\",\"terms\":\"Terms of Service\",\"contact\":\"Contact\",\"copyright\":\"© 2026 ToolPic. All rights reserved.\"}},\"now\":\"$undefined\",\"timeZone\":\"Asia/Shanghai\",\"children\":[\"$L14\",\"$L15\",\"$L16\"]}]\n17:I[1888,[\"707\",\"static/chunks/707-a8cb8823e74114e8.js\",\"450\",\"static/chunks/app/%5Blocale%5D/layout-8ce825e7014413b5.js\"],\"default\"]\n14:[\"$\",\"$L17\",null,{}]\n15:[\"$\",\"main\",null,{\"className\":\"flex-1\",\"children\":[\"$\",\"$L2\",null,{\"parallelRouterKey\":\"children\",\"error\":\"$undefined\",\"errorStyles\":\"